==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hypermeter
<hw>Hy*per"me*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ beyond
all measure; <grk>"ype`r</grk> over, beyond + <?/ measure: cf. F.
<ets>hyperm⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Pros.)</fld>
<def>A verse which has a redundant syllable or foot; a hypercatalectic
verse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, anything exceeding the ordinary
standard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When a man rises beyond six foot, he is an
<qex>hypermeter</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypermetrical</ent>⟦br⟧
